                </div>
                <div class="padding-left-40 padding-right-40">
                    {# CHALLENGES #}
                    <h2 class="c-learn-article-page__paragraph-heading">Challenges</h2>
                    <p class="c-learn-article-page__paragraph">
                        Your innovation name and the occasion / perfect serve will embody your value proposition. They
                        are key to convey what makes your innovation unique. Do not hesitate to give them some extra
                        thought while in test & learn stages. Naming especially: giving a name to an offer is complex as
                        it will remain the same once in market. Think longevity and stickiness!
                    </p>
                    {# QUESTIONS #}
                    <h2 class="c-learn-article-page__paragraph-heading">8 Questions to have in mind</h2>
                    <ul class="c-learn-article-page__list">
                        <li>Can I clearly express my unique value proposition in a tweet (141 characters)?</li>
                        <li>In 3 bullet points, can I say how my innovation is unique and different from what already
                            exists?
                        </li>
                        <li>Have I tested it with people around? (early adopters, friends & family, colleagues at work,
                            community from an existing online platform, people attending festivals…): do they understand
                            the idea without needing to give more details? Do they understand the benefit they get from
                            it?
                        </li>
                        <li>Does the name clearly communicate the benefit or personality of your Innovation?</li>
                        <li>The Usage: Do you understand the best way to experience it? Perfect Serve (for products
                            only) ‘the best way to drink it’ (eg spritz)
                        </li>
                        <li>Name clearly transmitting value at a point of purchase / plus pack for products only</li>
                        <li>Nuggets & Disruptive assets highlighting ‘reason to buy’, what clear and aspirational
                            nuggets does capture consumers' attention? How will it get naturally share of voice?
                        </li>
                        <li>Simple and unique value proposition, do you know how to transmit simply value to consumers?
                            Does it satisfy entirely new set of needs that consumers previously didn't perceive? Is the
                            newness clearly understood, straight forward? Any unfair competitive advantage?
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
